From: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] hw/misc/applesmc: add boot-required keys
 HE0N/HE2N/WDTC and platform identity

macOS reads a handful of additional SMC keys during early boot
and during graphics power-management init. Missing keys return
zero (patch 1) which is handled, but the following are worth
having concrete definitions for:

  * HE0N, HE2N - iGPU / dGPU power-enable. The AGPM driver
    reads these at init; without them macOS can enter a retry
    cascade on dynamic wallpaper changes. The drivers themselves
    write the final value, so the boot-time default of 0 is
    correct.
  * WDTC - watchdog timer control. Queried during early boot;
    an unanswered query produces a cluster of SMCWDT errors.
  * MPRO, MPRD, LGPB, BSLN, EPCI, BEMB - platform-identity keys
    exposed by VirtualSMC and consumed by X86PlatformPlugin.
  * OSWD, MSSW, RGEN, DPLM, $Adr - probed by the boot-time SMC
    client; $Num is kept as a VirtualSMC-compatible total-keys
    key alongside the canonical #KEY added in patch 2.
  * MSDW, NTOK - macOS sometimes writes these; declare them so
    subsequent reads of the written value work through the
    standard AppleSMCData storage.
  * CLKH, DICT, RPlt, SBFL, VRTC, WKTP - SMC-internal
    bookkeeping keys that are polled by the SMC client but
    carry no meaningful value on a VM.

Signed-off-by: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
---
 hw/misc/applesmc.c | 59 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 59 insertions(+)

--- a/hw/misc/applesmc.c
+++ b/hw/misc/applesmc.c
@@ -561,8 +561,59 @@
     applesmc_add_key(s, "PfST", 2, "\x00\x00");
     applesmc_add_key(s, "PSTR", 2, "\x00\x00");
     applesmc_add_key(s, "PHDC", 2, "\x00\x00");
+
+    /*
+     * GPU power-management keys. Without HE2N the AGPM driver reads
+     * NOEXIST, errors out (0x82) and hangs the system on dynamic
+     * wallpaper changes. The driver itself sets the value to 1 on
+     * start, so the boot default of 0 is correct.
+     */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "HE2N", 1, "\x00");
 
     /*
+     * Watchdog timer control. Queried by macOS during early boot; an
+     * unanswered query produces a cluster of SMCWDT errors per boot.
+     */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "WDTC", 1, "\x00");
+
+    /* Platform-identity keys also provided by VirtualSMC. */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "MPRO", 1, "\x01");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "MPRD", 1, "\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "LGPB", 1, "\x00");
+
+    /* CPU/power keys consumed by X86PlatformPlugin. */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "BSLN", 1, "\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "EPCI", 4, "\x00\x00\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "BEMB", 1, "\x01");
+
+    /* Keys read by the boot-time SMC probe. */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "OSWD", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "MSSW", 1, "\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "RGEN", 1, "\x02");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "DPLM", 4, "\x00\x00\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "$Adr", 4, "\x00\x00\x03\x00");
+
+    /* SMC internal bookkeeping. */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "CLKH", 1, "\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "DICT", 1, "\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "RPlt", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "SBFL", 1, "\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "VRTC", 2, "\x00\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "WKTP", 2, "\x00\x00");
+
+    /* Write targets that must also be readable. */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "HE0N", 1, "\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "MSDW", 1, "\x00");
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "NTOK", 1, "\x00");
+
+    /*
+     * VirtualSMC-compatible total-keys key. Kept for compatibility with
+     * drivers that look for $Num; the canonical Apple #KEY added in an
+     * earlier patch is what macOS actually iterates against.
+     */
+    applesmc_add_key(s, "$Num", 4, "\x00\x00\x00\x5e");
+
+    /*
      * #KEY - Apple SMC convention for "total key count". macOS reads
      * this at boot and iterates 0..count-1 via
      * APPLESMC_GET_KEY_BY_INDEX_CMD. Without it, macOS falls back to
